          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": " to restrict financial managers’ authority to move workers’ retirement savings into socially responsible and environmentally sustainable investments (known as ESG). He declared that “retirement plans are not vehicles for furthering social goals or policy objectives that are not in the financial interest of the plan” -- a statement implying that green investments are automatically at odds with the goal of maximizing returns, even though ",
